Auth: passwordless email-OTP via SMTP, no signup, skippable first-login onboarding

- /auth/signin is now one email field -> Continue -> 6-digit OTP emailed via SMTP
  (nodemailer, SMTP_* env) -> verify. Same screen for new + returning users; if the
  email has no account one is created automatically (emailVerified=now), else sign in.
- First login ONLY: a skippable welcome step (Name + Contact, prominent "Skip for now")
  saved to profile via completeOnboarding; never blocks entry; editable later in /profile.
  Tracked by User.onboardedAt (set on complete OR skip); existing users backfilled.
- /auth/signup 301-redirects to /auth/signin; removed the signup page/form + register route.
- OTP: 6-digit, 10-min TTL, 5 attempts, 30s resend cooldown, HMAC-hashed at rest,
  per-IP + per-email rate limit, generic responses. Branded HTML OTP email; dev-code
  fallback only when SMTP is unset. "Continue with Google" only if configured.
- Schema migration (backfill-safe): User.email unique+required, phone+firstName optional,
  onboardedAt added; OtpRequest keyed by email. JWT sessions unaffected.
- Removed unused MSG91 SMS path; admin settings shows SMTP status.

Verified end-to-end (scripts/demo-auth.mts): verify -> auto-create -> needs-onboarding ->
skip -> returning login skips onboarding, all pass.

